<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,224,395]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,224,251]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zompro &amp; Fritzsche" authorityYear="1999" box="[408,571,224,250]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[408,571,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Lucihormetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes twelve species of robust cockroaches that were separated from the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" box="[225,345,261,286]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Hormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[225,345,261,286]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Hormetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the presence of two very conspicuous protuberant yellow spots on pronotal disc. The name refers to bioluminescence of these yellow spots, but their luminosity is controversial till now (
<bibRefCitation author="Vrsansky, P. &amp; Chorvat, D. A. &amp; Fritzsche, I. &amp; Hain, M. &amp; Sevcik, R." pageId="7" pageNumber="162" pagination="739 - 749" refId="ref6631" refString="Vrsansky, P., Chorvat, D. A., Fritzsche, I., Hain, M. &amp; Sevcik, R. (2012) Light-mimicking cockroaches indicate Tertiary origin of recent terrestrial luminescence. Naturwissenschaften, 99 (9), 739 - 749. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00114 - 012 - 0956 - 7" type="journal article" year="2012">
Vršanský 
<emphasis box="[1380,1429,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vrsansky, P. &amp; Chorvat, D." box="[221,517,332,359]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" pagination="1099 - 1101" refId="ref6698" refString="Vrsansky, P. &amp; Chorvat, D. (2013) Luminescent system of Lucihormetica luckae supported by fluorescence lifetime imaging. Naturwissenschaften, 100 (11), 1099 - 1101. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00114 - 013 - 1100 - z" type="journal article" year="2013">Vršanský &amp; Chorvát 2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Greven, H. &amp; Zwanzig, N." box="[528,810,332,359]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" pagination="77 - 97" refId="ref5921" refString="Greven, H. &amp; Zwanzig, N. (2013) Courtship, Mating, and Organisation of the Pronotum in the Glowspot Cockroach Lucihormetica verrucosa (Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1865) (Blattodea: Blaberidae). Entomologie Heute, 25, 77 - 97." type="journal article" year="2013">Greven &amp; Zwanzig 2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Merritt, D. J." box="[821,968,332,359]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" pagination="697 - 698" refId="ref6177" refString="Merritt, D. J. (2013) Standards of evidence for bioluminescence in cockroaches. Naturwissenschaften, 100 (7), 697 - 698. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00114 - 013 - 1067 - 9" type="journal article" year="2013">Merritt 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
